SCMs allow to identify causal directions also within a Markov equivalence class, if certain assumptions on the structural form of the underlying process are fulfilled. Shown here (see Figure, panel e) is the LiNGAM approach (explained in Fig. 2d) which can be adapted to time series and assumes that the model is linear and at least one of the noise terms is non-Gaussian. Here, LiNGAM can identify the linear causal influence Yt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
